"We are pleased to announce that on July 26, 106 Russians were able to return home on Yerevan-Rostov-on-Don flights," TASS quoted the report as saying.
The embassy noted that the process of check-in and boarding of passengers on the flight was coordinated by diplomats.
In total, since the introduction of restrictions on flights, 2822 Russian citizens have been taken out of Armenia.
At the same time, on July 24, Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin announced the opening of air links with a number of countries from August 1.
Kirilenko shared his memories of games with Bryant and Jordan in the NBA
The head of the Russian Basketball Federation (RFB) Andrei Kirilenko shared his memories of his games against the legendary Kobe Bryant and Michael Jordan in the matches of the National Basketball Association (NBA).
I knew that Bryant's ego couldn't be hurt by some trash talk so as not to stimulate his athletic anger.
Kobe had a killer instinct, so on the court I tried to talk him in such a way that he did not perceive the game in an aggressive way.
On the set, I complimented him: "Oh!
Kobe, well scored, great pass!
Listening to my enthusiastic responses, he slightly forgot that he needed to pick up the ball once again and score another 3 - 4 points.
We communicated well with Kobe," Kirilenko was quoted as saying by Vechernyaya Moskva.
He also talked about his first game against Jordan.
"I took care of him.
For the first three minutes of the match, I ran around in complete awe of the fact that next to me was a legend that I had only seen on TV.
While my breath was running out of joy in my goiter, Michael scored a lot of points.
Soon I moved away from the excitement, a couple of times covered his shots...
In that game, my team won, and Jordan still scored 44 points," the head of the RFB added.
In the NBA, Kirilenko spent 12 seasons.
He was selected by the Utah Jazz in the 1999 NHL Entry Draft with the 24th overall pick.
In addition to Utah, for which he spent ten seasons, the Russian forward played for the Minnesota Timberwolves and Brooklyn Nets.
In total, he has played 797 games, in which he averaged 11.8 points, 5.5 rebounds, 2.7 assists and 1.8 blocks.
Earlier it was reported that Kirilenko will nominate his candidacy for the election of the head of the RFB.
Degtyarev was surprised by the information about the purchase of Gas "Sakhalin-1" for dollars
Acting Governor of the Khabarovsk Territory Mikhail Degtyarev on Sunday, July 26, during a meeting with residents of Sovetskaya Gavan, was surprised that the region buys Sakhalin gas produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas for dollars.
American gas is contracted in dollars until 2025.
"To be honest, I didn't know that and I'm in such a knockdown because of this information.
I had no idea that this is still possible in 2020 in Russia," RIA Novosti quoted him as saying.
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Ministry of Energy of Russia Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
The acting governor also stressed that by 2025 Gazprom will switch to supplying Russian thermal power plants and capacities, which means that Russian gas purchased in rubles "at normal prices" will be used.
The Sakhalin-1 project is being implemented through a production sharing agreement, where Exxon Neftegas Ltd is the project operator with a 30% stake, Rosneft has another 20%, Japan's Sodeco has 30% and India's ONGC has 20%.
The Khabarovsk Territory has been acquiring gas from this project since 2005.
